VARIABLES

You need an @ at the front of a variable if you want to be able to see that in a view

DATABASE

Databases always need to be plural and lowercase (seperated by underscores if multiple words)

ACTIVE RECORD

classes always need to be CamelCase - Uppercase first letter, capital letter for every word after. e.g. MacComputer and they need to be singular

ASSOCIATIONS

If a table has a has_many relationship

@plant.butterflies (name is always plural (normally the name of the table))

If a table has a belongs_to relationship

@butterfly.plant  (name is always singular (normally the lower case version of the class))
